The PredatOBR 7.62 was designed for those who are searching for a hybrid cross between the standard OBR and PredatAR 7.62x51 Rifles. The most remarkable feature of the PredatOBR is its ability to be completely "broken down" and stored into the toolbox. The PredatOBR handguard has locking stainless steel QD lever system on each side. Once the levers are released, the handguard slides off the upper assembly in seconds. The PredatOBR's barrel can easily be removed with the supplied PredatOBR Barrel Wrench, unscrew the barrel nut from the receiver and pull the barrel assembly free from the receiver. No need to remove the gas tube, gas block or muzzle device. Reverse the process to reinstall. Hand-tighten Barrel Nut and torque approximately 1/8-turn past hand-tight (Approximately 40-50 foot pounds). Once reassembled correctly, the point of impact (POI) shift will be 0.0 to 0.5 MOA of the original.PredatOBR barrels are chambered in 7.61x51mm, and feature rifling in a 1/10 twist rate. All barrels are threaded in 5/8x24. Like the OBR and PredatAR rifles, Larue Tactical has eliminated the conventional AR barrel nut and bolt the handguard directly to the proprietary upper receiver, creating a true "free-float" barrel. The handguard does not touch the barrel or barrel nut at any place. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day-night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet aluminum for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though it has been lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy.The PredatOBR has threaded stainless-steel hard-points over the entire length of the handguard at the 3, 6, and 9 o'clock positions. These hard-points have an integral spine built-in structural support. Provided with the system are three 3-inch MIL-STD-1913 rail sections that can be positioned anywhere along the handguard, per operator preference. These rail sections are attachable / detachable using a supplied tool. The rail sections are CNC-machined from billed aluminum. This robust solution provides a perfect precision mounting space for aiming lasers, illumination and bipods.The PredatOBR's  Port Selector Technology (PST) gas block is adjustable, to aid in the optimum function when using a sound suppressor. This special gas block contains a dual port mechanism that is operated by rotating a lever from one side to another. When the lever is rotated to the right-side of the rifle, the gasses are reduced, to compensate for the extra blowback created by the suppressor. When rotated to the left side, the gasses are increased for use without a suppressor.The Larue Tactical 6-position Retract Action Trigger (R.A.T) Stock comes standard with every PredatOBR. It is ergonomic, has protected control surfaces and contains a set of cleaning rods in an internal compartment. Since the height of the 12 o'clock rail is at the optimum position, there is no need for a cheek riser as part of this system.SpecificationsCaliber  7.62x51mm Nato  Barrel Length  18"  Rifling Twist Rate  1/10  Barrel Life  10,000 (approximately)  Gas System  Direct Impingement with Larue PST port selector  Trigger  Larue MBT
